Two foreigners among three drug dealers arrested19 July 2022KUALA LUMPUR - A local man and two foreign men believed to be drug dealers were arrested in raids involving 20 entertainment centers around the capital from Thursday to Saturday.Kuala Lumpur Police Chief Datuk Azmi Abu Kassim said the three-day raid was carried out from 11pm to 5am.According to him  the raid was carried out by a team of members from the Narcotics Criminal Investigation Department of the Kuala Lumpur Contingent Police Headquarters (IPK)  assisted by the Bukit Aman Narcotics Criminal Investigation Department  the Integrity and Compliance Department of the Kuala Lumpur Standards (JIPS KL) and the District Police Headquarters throughout Kuala Lumpur."Three men believed to be drug suppliers comprised of one local citizen  one Iranian and another was a Bangladeshi national " he said in the raid."In addition  918 individuals were examined while 180 individuals were also detained under various drug offences " he said in a statement on Tuesday.He said various drugs were also seized  including cocaine  methylenedioxy-methamphetamine (MDMA) powder  ecstasy and eryamine 5."In addition  three summonses under section 4(1)(b) of the Federal Territory Entertainment Act were issued for the offence of not having a valid business license " he said.According to him  the arrests were carried out under Section 39B of the Dangerous Drugs Act 1952  Section 12(2) of the Dangerous Drugs Act 1952 and Section 12(2) of the Dangerous Drugs Act 1952.
